WEBVTT

00:02:58.870 --> 00:03:01.234
And that continues to be the primary goal.

00:03:01.258 --> 00:03:05.123
But it also enables me to invent
with the technologies of the future,

00:03:05.147 --> 00:03:08.768
because I don't have the computers
of 20 years from now,

00:03:08.792 --> 00:03:11.005
but I can write about
what the impact will be.

00:03:11.592 --> 00:03:13.928
Chris Anderson: What is it
about the modern world

00:03:13.952 --> 00:03:17.521
that has driven that exponential increase?

00:03:17.545 --> 00:03:18.945
Why does that happen?

00:03:20.140 --> 00:03:22.220
RK: Well, that's a very good question.

00:03:22.244 --> 00:03:24.845
I don't think we fully understand that.

00:03:24.869 --> 00:03:30.103
For one thing, it's human nature to try
to increase things multiplicatively.